The administration also reached into the most vulnerable corners of the immigration system. It revoked humanitarian parole for a four-year-old Mexican girl receiving life-saving care in California, despite warnings that she could die within days without treatment. It canceled a major bird flu vaccine contract with Moderna, forfeiting priority access to doses in a future pandemic. It ordered consulates worldwide to halt student visa interviews while it designed a new regime of social media vetting, and it announced plans to \'93aggressively revoke\'94 visas for Chinese students, especially those in sensitive fields. These moves combined public health risk with a message. Access to safety, education, and mobility would be rationed along lines of nationality, politics, and perceived loyalty.\
