The culture war extended beyond classrooms. The administration targeted diversity, equity, and inclusion programs at military academies, leading to the disbanding of student clubs for women, Latinx students, and LGBTQ cadets, and the removal of books and materials deemed out of line with new policies. Trump wore a red campaign hat at West Point\'92s graduation and delivered partisan remarks at both West Point and Arlington National Cemetery, breaking long-standing norms of military and memorial neutrality. States like Utah, Idaho, and Montana enacted bans on flying LGBTQ flags at government buildings and schools during Pride month, imposing fines for violations. Corporate sponsors, wary of the administration\'92s stance on DEI and trans rights, pulled back from Pride events, forcing organizers to rely more on community support.\
